reviewText: I had heard of Pablo Francisco, years back he even toured smaller comedy clubs, and I had wanted to check him out... but never got the chance. Enter this DVD. What was an impulse buy at (forgive me, I attend college in a small town that doesn't even have a Best Buy) Wal-Mart, has instantly become one of my favorites discs. This guy does stand-up in a truly unique way, at no point in his act does he ever appear to be having anything but a good time. I can appreciate anyone who loves their job that much! Plus the guy's freakin' hilarious. Buy this DVD! Don't forget to pack a change of underwear. ;)
Title: Pablo Francisco - Bits And Pieces: Live From Orange County

reviewText: His comedy is right on, I first saw him on the Comedy channel and then on You Tube.  I found myself playing his bits over and over for family and friends.  Finally I decided I had to see his whole show, you will not be diappointed.
Title: Pablo Francisco - Bits And Pieces: Live From Orange County

reviewText: This is what got me in to stand-up comedy. This special is just as good when I watch it today as 5 years ago. Great stories, insane punch-lines and a finish that leaves you gasping for air. Remember to watch Pablo's commentary of the show, it's almost better than the main event. He does sound-effects to his own show-hilarious!
summary: Raising the bar for all other comics
Title: Pablo Francisco - Bits And Pieces: Live From Orange County

reviewText: Pablo definitely knows his stuff, and the material here is fairly funny for the most part. Be warned though, he uses a TON of profanity in here. Seeing him on TV, I thought he was relatively clean. That's not the case. Most of his jokes rely on profanity for the punchline. To see a much better job done with a lot less language, get anything by Brian Regan.
Title: Pablo Francisco - Bits And Pieces: Live From Orange County

reviewText: While most Americans do not know who he is, Pablo Francisco gained national attention in the late 1990s when he became a regular performer on MADtv. After his stint at Fox, he appeared in other TV shows doing live stand-up comedy and went on tour with Carlos Mencia and the late Freddy Soto. He still maintains a busy schedule performing around the country, especially at his favorite venue, the Improv in Los Angeles where many famous American comedians have performed.In this DVD, Francisco gives his most brilliant comedic performance. His vocal impressions of famous personalities, combined with his ability to devise ridiculous yet hilarious situations, make him a pleasure to watch. For example, he impersonates Don LaFontaine to simulate a fictional movie trailer about Arnold Schwarzenegger fighting the Italian mafia's encroachments on his tortilla-selling business.Throughout Bits and Pieces, Francisco jokes about many things like strip club dancers, body piercings, NASCAR racing, Viagra users, Latino music, and softcore pornography. While he lacks the genius of comedians such as Richard Pryor, his work is still very funny. His ability to keep audience members in a continued state of laughter is a testament to his excellent comedic skills.
Title: Pablo Francisco - Bits And Pieces: Live From Orange County

Title: Pablo Francisco - Bits And Pieces: Live From Orange County

reviewText: Pablo Francisco is funny as hell. Pure and simple. He's got way different material than most comedians today and he uses sound effects he produces himself to make things funny. He has your typical comedian jokes about porn. But then he'll begin to talk about the music they play in porn. And his impressions are great too. Like of the guy who narrates the movie commercials is just brilliant and then doing an impression of Arnold Schwarzenegger selling tacos on TV. Stuff like that. This guy is a step behind George Carlin in my oppinion. Absolutely hilarious. A++++
summary: Funny As Hell. One of the Funniest Live Shows Ever.
Title: Pablo Francisco - Bits And Pieces: Live From Orange County

reviewText: Pablo Francisco is a funny comedian.  This DVD will provide some good laughs without being too raunchy.  I enjoyed it.

reviewText: If you don't know pablo then you are missing out on one of the rising comedians of today. I saw him live at the local improv and after that I absolutely had to buy his DVD. He puts on a good show. I laughed so hard when I first saw this I was sore the next day. Highly recommended.
